ported by more independent, contemporaneous, and directly observable evidence. The bullish case rests on disruption narratives that the physical market (inventory data, price action) is actively not confirming. The weight of evidence favors BEARISH at PLAUSIBLE conviction. [Consensus ALIGNED (Vote=BEARISH)]", 'regime': 'HIGH_VOLATILITY', 'volatility_sentiment': 'NEUTRAL', 'confidence': 0.8, 'price': 273.45, 'sma_200': 310.0375, 'expected_price': 273.45, 'predicted_return': 0.0, 'thesis_strength': 'PLAUSIBLE', 'conviction_multiplier': 1.0}, {'contract_month': '202612', 'prediction_type': 'DIRECTIONAL', 'direction': 'BEARISH', 'reason': "The debate resolves in favor of the Bear, though not at high conviction. Here is the evidence accounting:\n\nBEARISH SIGNALS (independent lines):\n1. AGRONOMIST: 78mm/131% average rainfall in Minas Gerais (Somar) explicitly cited by Barchart/Nasdaq as bearish for prices — yield-supportive conditions for a record crop. Confidence moderated to 0.65 due to flooding uncertainty, but the directional signal is intact.\n2. INVENTORY: ICE certified stock build +41,735 bags to 477,229 in 9 days (CocoaIntel) is operationally unambiguous and cannot be dismissed. Brazilian Feb exports +30.2% YoY (Cecafé) and global Jan exports +13.7% YoY (ICO) confirm supply is clearing into the market at elevated rates.\n3. MACRO: BRL weakening (USD/BRL +1.67% to 5.2580) incentivizes farmer selling in the near term, adding supply pressure.\n4. SENTIMENT/COT: Managed Money net longs at 99th COT percentile (MarketBulls, 2026-02-24) is a classic contrarian bearish signal — extreme crowding creates asymmetric downside risk on any catalyst for unwinding.\n5. MARKET STRUCTURE: Price at 269.25 is 11.0% below the 200-day SMA of 302.59, in a RANGE_BOUND regime with 0.80% 5-day volatility. The market has not confirmed any bullish reversal — the -1.09% 24h and 5-day trend is mild but directionally bearish.\n\nBULLISH SIGNALS (independent lines):\n1. GEOPOLITICAL/SHIPPING: 